my dogs sockets in her hips are square not round so she can not go up stairs or she can not go hunting it sounds like she has hip dysplasia you'll want to talk to your vet about treatments for it there are several medications and depending on her age etc sometimes surgery is an option sadly hip dysplasia is an issue for a lot of dogs the risks of hip dysplasia can be lowered by only breeding dogs that are ofa clear of the disease the causes of hip dysplasia also have been linked with obesity as well as early spay nueter long bones continue to grow for too long due to lack of hormone Hip dysplasia Prostate cancer Cancer Dog Growth hormone deficiency Growth hormone treatment Equine conformation Gastroesophageal reflux disease Hormone replacement therapy (trans) English Springer Spaniel Dwarfism Milk Cat Breast cancer Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Beagle Hip fracture Ferret Pet skunk Scoliosis Osteoarthritis Osteoporosis Great Dane Arrhythmogenic right ventricular dysplasia Border Collie Androgen insensitivity syndrome Livestock Growth hormone Guinea pig Cardiovascular disease American Cocker Spaniel Polycystic ovary syndrome Obesity Traumatic brain injury German Shepherd Dog Myelodysplastic syndrome Tibetan Terrier Cardiac arrhythmia Redbone Coonhound Diabetes mellitus Domestic rabbit Fancy rat Havanese Border Terrier Rhodesian Ridgeback Hip replacement Renal cell carcinoma Keeshond Alaskan Malamute Urinary incontinence Nutrition Acromegaly Spondyloepiphyseal dysplasia congenita Cervical cancer Paget's disease of bone Conjunctivitis Cephalic disorder Cushing's syndrome Hypoglycemia Chronic fatigue syndrome Hypertension Basset Hound Siberian Husky German Shorthaired Pointer Carpal tunnel syndrome Insulin Finnish Spitz Veterinarian Radiation therapy Hip hop culture Medicine Stomach cancer Labrador Retriever Metabolic syndrome Atkins Nutritional Approach English Setter Liger Ectopic pregnancy Sex reassignment surgery female-to-male Atherosclerosis Italian Greyhound Bernese Moun